The paper focuses on data provenance and lineage, which is a topic commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and database (cs.DB) communities. The use of blockchain technology also suggests a potential fit with the distributed computing (cs.DC) and internet of things (cs.IOT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the framework's integration and client library, which could be relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
